caption: Good food, but some of the menu items have poor food portions for the price. For example, 10 bucks only gets you a few pieces of chicken and some rice for the rice bowl dishes—don’t get these if you’re hungry. I’ve found the Namesake to be the only good deal with a good balance of protein and bread for the price.

Good food

Excited to hear about the restaurant opening to have local Vietnamese cuisine. Disappointed with catered banh mi sandwiches and wouldn’t recommend anyone looking for authentic Vietnamese cuisine. I tried the pork sandwich and it was filled with shredded carrots and few slices of Chinese roasted pork. Only Vietnamese aspect is the cold/soggy French baguette and sparsely spread of pate.  Who uses chicken in banh mi? I guess this Bon Me place. Talk about false advertising. They should remove “Vietnamese” from their description because this is so far from authentic.
Tasty, vegan options.  Not much ambience.
Rude staff. Half the items from their menu on their website are not offered at this location.
Not too many choices

I love the sandwiches!  I love that they have a small curated menu so they can work fast during the lunch rush and still produce a quality product. The rotating proteins let you try something new each time!

This place was no good to me. They have really sacrificed a lot by trying to Americanize Vietnamese food. Authentic Vietnamese is already so delicious, the owner should stick to the good stuff instead of this crappy alternative fusion style. My vermicelli noodles were missing on texture and flavor, and the tofu was tasty, but bad temperature and texture. S disappointing. Also my Vietnamese Iced coffee was awful, boba was old and hard, and thai tea was extremely watered down. I cannot understand how they get away with charging $7 for a banh mi sandwich. Should cost less than $5, preferably $3. And the flavor didn't merit the price. I gave this place 2 tries, will not return for a third. If they fix the problems mentioned maybe I will return.
Always has lines. Always tasty. Always will be around. Try this truck when u see it.

Love this place but the portion is inconsistent. I come here everyday and the amount of food they give is different. Also don't order extra meat. I have ordered extra meat a few time and never got any extra. Hope the owner can see this.
This is a lunch place you can go when you don't know what to eat. Americanise Vietnamese food.

Boba tea and bubbles are really great! Not too expensive, and some of the best that I've tasted in Cambridge. Limited flavors, but the flavors that they have are very good. The boba is very chewy and not mushy.

Bon Me = zero risk deliciousness. Go there and order anything you want, and you'll leave satisfied.
Had the Chinese BBQ pork sandwich. It was only $6 and it was wonderful! Great bread...tender pork....fresh vegetables

I really enjoyed my experience at Bon Me! Although the menu is small, it's comprehensive, friendly and super delicious. Out goal was to sit outside in the sunshine and the food was perfectly packaged for transport and outdoor eating. I tried the salad with the spicy peanut dressing (a great kick to it!), spicy tofu which was both soft with crunchy sides and a deviled tea egg. I would encourage a little more flavor for the tea egg but otherwise all components were tasty, fresh and well prepared! Certainly recommend for a fun lunch spot and super friendly folks! :)

This review is for the food truck at Harvard Yard (which doesn't show up on Local)  I had the salad with spice rub chicken - I am a customer for life. Best of all, the food truck took credit cards (via Square)!  The food was good, but I have to remove a star because I think for $7 I didn't get as much food as I would had liked - especially since my base dish was a salad, which I imagine would tack on merely a couple of cents to their COGS if they added a bit more to the box.

This is for the food truck: If I pay $2.50 for hard boiled eggs with sauce, I expect more than one egg. Maybe that's because the sign did say 'eggs', maybe that's just me wanting more because they were the only good thing I got. I would go back for that.  Salad was overdressed and I could hardly eat it by the time I got back to work. I'm surprised the bottom of the box didn't give out.  Ginger lemonade was okay, a bit too much on the ginger side for me, as I didn't get much lemon. If it was called gingerade....
great food, go there all the time
Fantastic in every way. Rice bowls are awesome..and the Bon Me sandwich the best around!!
